The paper proposes an image-based facial reenactment system that uses image retrieval and face transfer techniques. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves motion analysis and facial expression recognition, which are also common topics in graphics (cs.GR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The system is designed to work with off-the-shelf cameras, which suggests a focus on human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves machine learning techniques for image matching, which suggests a possible connection to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
